# road_to_professional

# looking for solo developers to learn together, jam, compete, and accountability

Are you looking to be a professional solo developer? Are you willing to work hard to achieve that goal? Would you like to join a small team of solo devs all learning the craft together?

I am mainly a programmer, who is aiming to be a generalist game developer as I have interest in both the logical and creative side of game development. I also have a gamedev youtube channel with a humble 100 subscribers, so marketing and other aspects of gamedev will not be neglected!

Hi I am starting a server of solo developers who could commit to learning with accountability and doing jams individually we all submit our own jams mainly but still having a small server of supportive devs for ideas, motivation, constructive criticism and feedback. The end goal of being better solo developers.

Looking for kind, supportive, hard working, wholesome people!

You can be any kind of dev, an artist, programmer, musician, writer. You can team up and jam in the server if you want and there is availability, but the main focus is solo jams as that is more reliable and also you get all the credit. You can use things like renpy, make programmer art, text based games, etc.

I'm thinking of having 2 parts to the server. 

One is the Performance team where we would expect more regular messages (at least a substantial message once a week e.g. "I played your game jam entry and found a subtle bug" rather than "hey what's up?"), this is more by feel rather than by measure. Also participation in jams (at least every 3-6 months though ideally every month).

The Regular team is basically open to anyone interested in game development but doesn't want to commit to a more immersive game jam team, this is totally fine and I would still like to support them.

Please DM me if interested and/or reply to this message. Thank you for your time. 

